	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Gameboy DMG-01 Hardware Issue</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Unfortunately, the DMG is a sufficiently integrated device (CPU, joypad, PPU, sound, link port, bootstrap ROM) that repair is a long shot.<br /><br />Try without a cart. Even without one there should be a scrolling black rectangle when it's turned on.<br /><br />Your description says to me that the power supply correctly generates -19V, and the LCD driver gets a few clocks, and then nothing else.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


